&lt;p&gt;During my master&amp;rsquo;s program at TUM, I participated in a team project focused on developing a service robot to serve drinks. The robot was designed to go to the service point, listen to people&amp;rsquo;s requests (i.e., which drink they wanted), then navigate to a shelf, recognize the requested drink, retrieve it, and bring it back to the customer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This project encompassed several key areas of knowledge, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Speech recognition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigation using SLAM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Object identification and neural network training with YOLO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Robot manipulation using MoveIt&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
